f of the book explores how a richer set of ideas about policing might change our thinking about a range of problems and controversies associated with the police, ranging from racial profiling and the proliferation of private security, to affirmative action and the internal governance of law enforcement agencies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476322640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804763226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804763226/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles